title: For Sale:  Ithica 1911 A1 .45 ACP WWII
postcontent:
This is a WWII Ithica 1911A1 45 auto.
 After a couple of  hours on a website called coolgunsite.com, and a couple of other sites,  I have learned that this pistol was :  Made in 1943, has the proper High Standard barrel, Has the proper Keys grips, has the proper checkered mainspring housing, Has a magazine made by Little manufacturing  ( WWII supplier ), Is stamped with AA  for either Anniston Arsenal, or Agusta Arsenal.  This pistol was purchased from the government , via the NRA,  according to the older gentalman that sold it to me. He could  not find the paperwork.  It has most of the finish still on the gun. There are a lot of small pitts under the finish on the slide, and some on the frame as well. ( I assume that 's why it went through an arsenal ). The bore is shiny. There seems to be very little wear on the pistol, except at the sharp edges. I have not fired it, but it seems to function well.
 Please feel free to ask for more pictures or any questions. I believe this to be an honest example of a WWII 45.
 No Calif sales. Face to face in Oklahoma with proper Drivers liscense
